parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seatbelt can cause injury or death in the event of an accident, as well as discomfort and difficulty breathing due to excessive tightening.
symptoms: The seatbelt tightens around the passenger's chest or neck
making it difficult to breathe or move
the seatbelt separates from the panel
the seatbelt locks the passenger in
the seatbelt becomes detached during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt buckle can cause injury or death in the event of an accident, as well as difficulty releasing the buckle.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle will not release

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seatbelt can cause injury or death in the event of an accident, as well as difficulty securing car seats.
symptoms: The rear seatbelts do not properly retain car seats
allowing free side-to-side movement while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt release button can cause injury or discomfort.
symptoms: The driver's thumb is cut when depressing the release button of the driver's shoulder belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause sudden loss of power, unexpected slowing, and difficulty shifting gears, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, and strand the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips upon takeoff and hard acceleration

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Defective Factory Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of defective factory parts can cause premature transmission failure, leading to unexpected repair costs, loss of vehicle use, and potential safety risks.
The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to unexpected shifting, loss of power, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Transmission failure to shift into reverse

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause electrical system failures, including fires, which can result in injuries or damage.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition switch
the key cannot be removed or turned in the ignition
the vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
smoke comes from the steering column or dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause electrical system failures, including fires, which can result in injuries or damage.
symptoms: Smoke comes from the steering column or dash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause potential accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle engine shuts down while driving
